<br>
What I'd like to propose in an effort to promote server honesty and accountability is to have people post their <br>
intentions no more than 2 days in advance. 2 days is arbitrary but I think that one day is too short and 48 hours is plenty of time to contact all the people you need to. Also, the shorter we keep peoples intentions (not reservations), the more likely people will be to honor those intentions.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I'd like to offer up a slightly more controversial suggestion. Basically, if someone is posting when a raid will occur and you think your plans are going to conflict with theirs, post up your intentions...very precisely. For example: &quot;Red Branch is planning on going to Fear this Thursday, we need one A blighted robe, almost a full set of carmine, Val BP, 2 Val Bracers, and a couple of TV bracers.&quot;<br>
<br>
What this does is that it gives people some indication of what mobs will be contested, and what negotiations need to take place.<br>
<br>
Also this could extend to Dracho and Cazic...sure every warrior wants a bloodfire or whatever, but if your goal is to drop him for a wizard FA skin, then the magnanimous thing would be to discuss that with whoever is up there.<br>
<br>
This server doesn't have to be a cesspool, it can be a place where people enjoy their time and the company of their neighbors...generally the best way to accomplish such an environment is with communication...and perhaps begin the conversation not assuming that your goals are always the most important ones..that's why we call it a MMOLRPG and not EQuake.<br>
<br>
Anyway, if you got this far, thanks for reading.<br>
<br>
